{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/brazen/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Developer's blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"078523e3-1ada-5a19-b85b-4aa3ec7de976","excerpt":"Meaning Brazen (adjective) means bold and shameless, often in a way that shows no respect for rules, social norms, or embarrassment. It can also describe…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#meaning\">Meaning</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\">Grammar and Usage</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#patterns\">Patterns</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#common-phrases\">Common Phrases</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#collocations\">Collocations</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#examples\">Examples</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\">Synonyms or Related</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","html":"<h2 id=\"meaning\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#meaning\" aria-label=\"meaning permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Meaning</h2>\n<p><strong>Brazen</strong> (adjective) means bold and shameless, often in a way that shows no respect for rules, social norms, or embarrassment. It can also describe something made of brass (less common in modern usage).</p>\n<h2 id=\"grammar-and-usage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\" aria-label=\"grammar and usage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Grammar and Usage</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Part of speech</strong>: Adjective</li>\n<li>Used to describe a person, behavior, or action that is shockingly bold or disrespectful.</li>\n<li>Can also be used as a verb (formal/literary): <em>to brazen something out</em> → to face a difficult or embarrassing situation with bold confidence.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"patterns\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#patterns\" aria-label=\"patterns permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Patterns</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><em>a brazen lie</em> (shamelessly obvious lie)</li>\n<li><em>a brazen act of theft</em> (open and bold act)</li>\n<li><em>to brazen it out</em> (to act as if nothing is wrong)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"common-phrases\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#common-phrases\" aria-label=\"common phrases permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Common Phrases</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>brazen lie</strong> – a lie told without shame</li>\n<li><strong>brazen act</strong> – a bold, shameless action</li>\n<li><strong>to brazen it out</strong> – to deal with a difficult or embarrassing situation by behaving confidently</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"collocations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collocations\" aria-label=\"collocations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collocations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>brazen attempt</strong></li>\n<li><strong>brazen disregard</strong></li>\n<li><strong>brazen confidence</strong></li>\n<li><strong>brazen thief</strong></li>\n<li><strong>brazen display</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>He told a <strong>brazen lie</strong> right to the teacher’s face.</li>\n<li>The thief made a <strong>brazen attempt</strong> to steal the necklace in broad daylight.</li>\n<li>She walked into the meeting late, with a <strong>brazen confidence</strong> that surprised everyone.</li>\n<li>Their <strong>brazen disregard</strong> for the rules shocked the community.</li>\n<li>Despite being caught, he decided to <strong>brazen it out</strong> and act innocent.</li>\n<li>The politician’s <strong>brazen behavior</strong> angered the public.</li>\n<li>His <strong>brazen attitude</strong> made him both admired and disliked.</li>\n<li>The company issued a <strong>brazen denial</strong> of the accusations.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"synonyms-or-related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\" aria-label=\"synonyms or related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Synonyms or Related</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Shameless</li>\n<li>Bold</li>\n<li>Audacious</li>\n<li>Unashamed</li>\n<li>Insolent</li>\n<li>Defiant</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"brazen meaning and examples","date":"2025-08-31","description":"English learning materials; brazen explanation.","tags":["English","adjective"],"featuredImage":{"publicURL":"/static/65c3875a54163381b38bb54fc3aa1d95/brazen.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8e8b8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/65c3875a54163381b38bb54fc3aa1d95/b5658/brazen.png","srcS